A = [1,2,2,3]
B = [2,2]
output: true

logic:
1. convert a into map of key as value and value as count
2. from the map check b exist , if exist check the count is there (i.e num should exist if count 0 then its not occuring multiple times same as A)
3. if count exist then reduce the count


class Solution {
    public boolean isSubset(int a[], int b[]) {
        // Your code here
        Map<Integer,Integer> aFreq= new HashMap<>();
        for(int j: a){
            aFreq.put(j, aFreq.getOrDefault(j,0)+1);
        }
        for (int i: b){
            if(!aFreq.containsKey(i) || aFreq.get(i)==0){
                
            
            return false;
            }
            aFreq.put(i, aFreq.getOrDefault(i,0)-1);
        }
        return true;
    }
}
